An **overdraft (OD) account** charges interest only on the amount you actually use, unlike a term loan where you pay on the full disbursed amount. OD interest is calculated daily on the outstanding balance. This makes OD accounts cost-efficient for businesses and individuals who need flexible access to funds rather than a fixed lump sum.
